    <h2>About Student Management</h2>

    <p>
        The <strong>Student Management System</strong> is a web-based application developed using the <strong>ASP.NET Core MVC</strong> framework.
        It provides a simple and effective interface to manage student records, including personal information and academic performance.
    </p>

    <h3>Key Features</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Create, read, update, and delete student records (CRUD)</li>
        <li>Upload and display profile images</li>
        <li>Store data such as name, gender, date of birth, and GPA</li>
        <li>Responsive layout for desktop and mobile</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Technology Stack</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>ASP.NET Core MVC</strong> – for application structure and routing</li>
        <li><strong>Razor Pages</strong> – for dynamic view rendering</li>
        <li><strong>SQL Server</strong> – for relational data storage</li>
        <li><strong>Entity Framework Core</strong> – for ORM-based database interaction</li>
        <li><strong>HTML5 & CSS3</strong> – for layout and styling</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Purpose</h3>
    <p>
        This project was created as a learning exercise in building real-world ASP.NET applications with SQL Server integration.
        It demonstrates how to connect a web UI to a database, perform CRUD operations, and manage images and form input securely.
    </p>

